      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the leak is elsewhere, you need more granular memory tracking without full profiler overhead. Implement custom memory hooks by overriding the global `new` and `delete` operators in your ECU build. Inside these overloaded functions, log the allocation size and call stack trace (if possible on your target) before the allocation occurs. This will capture every single memory request across the entire system, allowing you to trace allocations back to their source module.",
