      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To differentiate between one large growing object and many small leaks, observe the rate and pattern of memory increase over time. If the memory usage increases in large, discrete steps, you likely have a single, accumulating structure; if it grows smoothly and incrementally, you are probably losing many small allocations. You can also monitor the *system heap usage* itself, noting whether the growth is dominated by large blocks or many small blocks via your internal allocation hooks.",
